Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: I'm populating browser django components using on chain data storeid in oraclesCC. no reason you couldnt store the raw html, but seems more efficient to just use django templates which reference a batonutxo (or an array of batonutxos) to fill out the dynamic components.

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: There can be a load delay if grabbing too much data though. I clocked calling around 900 `oraclesinfo` at 42 sec (21.5 oracles/sec) which is too long for a webpage to load. workaround is to cron the data into a local json file for site to reference.
